			<div class="content" id="post-content-3672923">
									

<p><strong>Why do you feel you should be a junior staff? Why the Community Outreach team?</strong></p>
<p>I have been following/contributing to the site for almost two years now (14 days until exactly two years) and I have a very good grasp on the variety of articles and resources available on the site. Not only that, I enjoy interacting with people and find contests to be one of the most interesting parts of the wiki. In fact, they’re one of my favorite parts, if not my favorite part, and I often find myself browsing through some of the previous contests.</p>
<p><strong>How active are you?</strong></p>
<p>While my posting on the site may seem somewhat low, whether it’s checking out the forums, seeing and reading what’s been recently created, or looking at what’s happening in O5, I am active in some regard pretty much everyday. Furthermore, I am very active on IRC in multiple rooms and have been active on irc for over a year now.</p>
<p><strong>Which of the responsibilities listed above do you think you would be a good fit for and why?</strong></p>
<p>I believe that I would be good with speaking to newer members, discussing/creating contests, and helping with site news.</p>
<p>For newer members, I am a friendly individual, and would be good at pointing them in the right direction, both resource wise (in terms of guides, essays, and how to interact more with the community) and reading wise (in terms of SCPs, tales, and other such content), as well as just talking to them about their interests.</p>
<p>For discussing contest ideas, as I mentioned earlier they are one of my favorite parts of the wiki, and I would be good at brainstorming or fleshing our ideas.</p>
<p>For the site news, I enjoy reading articles a great deal and believe that would come in handy, especially with the small blurbs each one has, which I enjoy coming up with or finding.</p>
<p>Overall, I believe I would be a very good fit for community outreach JS, and regardless of whether or not I am accepted, thank you for the opportunity :)</p>

