<p><strong>Why do you feel you should be a junior staff? Why the Community Outreach team?</strong></p>
<p>I think I might like to be more involved in the community and, if possible, help with bearing the load of maintaining the site. I've been a member for about 2 years, and think I'm pretty familiar with the general lore and background of the Foundation universe; and (more importantly), with the culture and members of the community itself. Also, I can communicate effectively, and be mature when a situation calls for it.</p>
<p>While I understand the draft and feedback process, I don't feel my writing ability qualifies me for any Crit Team roles. So maybe this is a way to get into the scene and be helpful.</p>
<p><strong>How active are you?</strong></p>
<p>When I'm at work I usually have SCP wiki and #Site19 chat open in a couple background tabs. That's 12 hours (~10pm-10am Eastern) of as much attention as work allows. It's overnights and often quiet, so generally allows a decent amount.</p>
<p>I check in periodically on my time off as well. Frequency depending on what I'm following on the site, and my mobile data.</p>
<p><strong>Which of the responsibilities listed above do you think you would be a good fit for and why?</strong></p>
<p>I think I'd be well suited to interacting with newer members and pointing them in the direction of helpful resources. I'm familiar with the guides, and if I don't know something offhand then often enough I know where to find it. I reckon I know enough about the site to help a new user navigate and find their way.</p>
<p>Also I believe I have organizational ability and could solicit and keep track of user ideas for foreground events like contests or suggestions for background technical things. To help refine greater opinion into concise statements and direct them at the appropriate staff to be addressed. Or apply myself to whichever duties might be suitable.</p>
<p>I'd like to close with something cheeky like &quot;References available upon request&quot; but they wouldn't be, so&#8230; There's my application. Cheers!</p>

