			<div class="content" id="post-content-3674563">
									

<p>Here goes:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Why do you feel you should be a junior staff? Why the Community Outreach team?</strong></p>
<p>I care a lot about this site as a project - I believe that what we're doing here has important implications. It's a prototype on the cutting edge of how reading and storytelling will evolve in the 21st century, and an incredible source of free education, and a lot of other things I could go on about. At the same time, I also care about it as a bunch of welcoming and supportive people who have done a lot for me just by being here and doing this.</p>
<p>I'm interested in contributing to the administration/housekeeping of the project because it's a fascinating and significant thing; I'm interested in contributing to the culture of positivity and acceptance we have as a bunch of people because it's been invaluable to me personally (and is fascinating and significant in its own way). So applying to be community outreach staff makes sense.</p>
<p>I've been junior staff on the forum crit team since mid-October, and I think that's been going well. It's been an honor to be part of a team like this one, and I would love to continue finding uses for the skills I have to offer.</p>
<p><strong>How active are you?</strong></p>
<p>I check the forums (and O5) every day, frequently, though mostly for just a few minutes at a time. I post quite a bit - since I've recently moved far from home, this site's been a major source of social interaction for me, which is one of the reasons I'm so grateful for it. I make it a point to respond when newcomers (or anyone else) are trying to engage with the community, because I remember how good it felt when staff did the same for me.</p>
<p><strong>Which of the responsibilities listed above do you think you would be a good fit for and why?</strong></p>
<p><em>Posting in the Introductions threads on the forums, responding to new members and directing them to site resources</em> - I do a good bit of this already, for the reasons above. The resources we have here are unique, and it's exciting to see people introduced to them. I've contribited some successful and well-received tales while struggling when it comes to SCP articles themselves, so I can relate to both success and failure in writing here, and even have an extensive skill set related to helping people learn from challenges and frustration rather than give up.</p>
<p><em>Helping ProcyonLotor with soliciting contest ideas, discussing contests with moderators and admins, and hosting/organizing contests</em> - I think I could be helpful with this; designing and running activities to get people engaged in things is a big part of my job, so it would be interesting to apply that here.</p>
<p><em>Helping ARD produce the Monthly Site News</em> - On it! I'd say I'm doing a not-perfect-but-pretty-okay job at this so far, and plan to continue; it's a perfect task for me to chip away at bit by bit with my sporadic moments of free time.</p>
<p><em>Overseeing fan work, art, and projects</em> - I can probably help with this - really, I think the site has a lot of potential to be a learning + entertainment resource for art a lot like it is for writing, and I'd like to help that develop.</p>
<p><em>Soliciting ways to improve the site and following up on said ideas by talking to people on Tech Team, Internet Outreach, etc. etc.</em> - I'm completely useless on the technology end of things, but coordinating information to help run and improve organizations is something I'm experienced with. I think a lot about the site and how we could do even more with it than we already are, so having regular chances to discuss those ideas with the senior staff would be really exciting.</p>
<p>Thank you for reading all this! The site means a lot to me, and it was nice to have prompts to put some of it into words. Here's to taking it all even further in 2018.</p>
</div>
