<p><strong>Why do you feel you should be a junior staff? Why the Community Outreach team?</strong></p>
<p>Because I love this community and want to help make it a better and more enjoyable place. I've been in this community for more than a year at this point, and in that time the community has been a place that helped me get through the day. Writing, chatting, critting, etc. etc. It helped me. And, I think, it only makes sense to help make the community better by responding to feedback from the community itself. I wanna help with that. No point in loving a community if you don't wanna help it now and again.</p>
<p><strong>How active are you?</strong></p>
<p>I check the forums for both the SCP wiki and O5 on a daily, if not hourly, basis. I'm active in Site19, although during the weekday my time is significantly shortened compared to the weekends. I critique articles when I have the time to do them. I'm more active on chat than in the forums, however, as I've spent more time with IRC than I have with the forums.</p>
<p><strong>Which of the responsibilities listed above do you think you would be a good fit for and why?</strong></p>
<p>Talking with new members in the Introduction threads. I like interacting with new members of the community, finding out how they got onto the site, what they plan on doing in the site, and reading their drafts. The way you talk with a new member can affect the way they interact with the site, give them a good feeling about the site and the community at large.</p>
<p>Helping ARD with the Monthly news would also be a good fit for me. I could help provide the articles posted each month with an interesting tagline, something that could draw in a reader who wants to read something of that month. I'm a fast writer, so I'd be able to easily write them out when I get the time to sit down and actually write the news out.</p>
<p>Overseeing art and projects is another important thing I think I could help on. This site should be willing to put our artists of all backgrounds in the forefront, regardless of which format they decide to express their creativity - podcast, paintings, music, games, etc. etc. Hard work goes into all of these things, and these deserve to be given a spotlight just as we give a spotlight to our articles at the end of each month. I wanna make sure these artists get the proper recognition they deserve.</p>

