<p><strong>Why do you feel you should be a junior staff? Why the Community Outreach team?</strong></p>
<p>I thoroughly love this community and everything that comes with it. The wiki has made me a better writer and has expanded my passion for writing, and I am convinced that it can do the same for others. I'm convinced that the wiki can do the same for others, and I'd love to help with it. I love this place and I want to help out in any way that I possibly can.</p>
<p><strong>How active are you?</strong></p>
<p>I'm on chat pretty much every day for most of the day, talking with people and just generally having a good time. I monitor the forums throughout the day as well and check O5 fairly regularly. Whenever I have time/energy, I'll be doing my Forum Crit duties, making sure there isn't any significant backlog.</p>
<p><strong>Which of the responsibilities listed above do you think you would be a good fit for and why?</strong></p>
<p>I already welcome new members in the Introduction threads every now and then, showing some of them the forums and such. I actually enjoy doing that a lot, I think it shows a warm welcome that makes new members feel good.</p>
<p>I'm actually pretty decent at coming up with new ideas and I think that thinking of ways to improve the site would be a great fit for me. I've already got a few ideas that I think might reach out to the off-wiki fandom and make them feel more included in the wiki itself, and ideas that might make the overall community feel more involved and closer together.</p>
<p>I'd also love to help out with the monthly news- I'd like everyone to get credit for things that they've written, and I'd also like to help make sure that anything that might of got bumped off of &quot;.lc&quot; on chat or overlooked because of other new articles get some well-deserved attention. Everyone works hard for what they post to the site, and I think everyone deserves recognition for it.</p>

