			<div class="content" id="post-content-4262908">
									

<p>Greetings! <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1559067591" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;">A Random Day</a></span> here, captain of the Community Outreach team! We are currently seeking Junior Staff for the INTRODUCTIONS team!</p>
<p>The Introductions team is one of the core pillars of Community Outreach. Under the direction of team leader <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1613974); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1613974&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1559067591" alt="UraniumEmpire" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1613974)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1613974); return false;">UraniumEmpire</a></span>, your job is to reply to new posts in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-72352/introductions">monthly sticked Introductions threads</a>, greeting new users and directing them to site resources and articles that will enrich their experience with the site and help them enjoy their time spent!</p>
<p><strong>Primary Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Posting in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-11499557/may-2019-intros-explorers">Explorers</a>, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-11499548/may-2019-intros-writers">Writers</a>, and <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-11499566/may-2019-intros-readers-reviewers">Reviewers</a> threads on the forums and responding to new members and directing them to site resources</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Competitive Perks:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>After ~2-3 months on the team, <em>we are able to nominate you for promotion to fully Operational Staff</em> (which occurs every 4 months). (Note: If we choose not to nominate you, and you're curious why, we will try to be completely open with you about it.)</li>
<li>An experience of staff ongoings, such as policy discussion and other staff shenaningans.</li>
<li>The ability to post to the staff site. You won't be responsible for voting or anything but can give your view on policies relevant to Community Outreach.</li>
<li>No pressure- if it's not for you, there's nothing forcing you to keep at it.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>If you're interested, please <em>REPLY TO THIS POST</em> with the following information:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Why do you want to be a junior staff on Community Outreach?</p>
<p>How active are you?</p>
<p>How can we contact you? Wikidot, IRC, and/or Discord?</p>
</blockquote>

