			<div class="content" id="post-content-4330599">
									

<p>Okay hullo, I'm fairly new and I only have a couple pages BUT</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">here&nbsp;are&nbsp;the&nbsp;reasons</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Why do you want to be a junior staff on Community Outreach?</strong></p>
<p>Probably the biggest reason I'm attracted to this position in the first place is that I actually had a real life job doing this kind of thing. I used to work for my school's fine arts college organizing, planning and running workshops and events. I even moderated a few of them myself.<br />
I'm not a super great writer or critter, but I have practical experience in this area specifically and my organization/time management skills are pretty rock solid, and I'd like to think that could be useful!</p>
<p>((Oh and obviously I love it here and think that workshops are a great avenue to bring folks together and share knowledge so of course I'd love to contribute to an environment where learning is so readily encouraged, <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">I'm not going to get sappy about friendship and artistic self-improvement I promise</span>))</p>
<p><strong>How active are you?</strong></p>
<p>I'm on the site nearly every day. I have to check it a lot because a lot of my commission correspondence comes through here.</p>
<p><strong>Can we contact you via Wikidot, IRC, and/or Discord?</strong></p>
<p>Wikidot pm and Discord are safe bets!</p>
</div>
